race.comment: MELDUBIOUS (3) may have suffered from the dreaded second-up syndrome last time out but the form prior was full of merit. Is one from one over this track and trip and sharp improvement would not surprise. JENCHICK BOOM (8) goes well for hoop Jones who is yet to miss a place in five steers. Has a handy record over this six-furlong journey and should give backers a sight. FORTUNEER (1) resumes here but has a solid fresh record with a win and three placings from five attempts. Can run a race first-up. I'M ZAC (6) has won two from three when fresh and may make his presence felt. BUNDELLA (2) best of the rest with the 3kg claim.
